    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Rear Body Exterior Lights and Warning Lights</title>
        <para>The exterior lights and warning light assemblies and lenses at the rear of the bus body may be totally
            removed due to damage.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bulb replacement is done by removing the eight lens mounting screws on the applicable light,
                removing the lens and seal, and replacing the bulb.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The entire light fixture may be removed by removing the lens (step 1), and locating the
                light fixture mounting screws.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47005123" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g47005123.webp" filename="../figg47/G47005123.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 123. Typical Light Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">STOP / TAIL LIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">AMBER DIRECTIONAL LIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">TYPICAL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">STANDARD BACK-UP LIGHT</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">DIRECTION / TURN SIGNAL LIGHT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mounting screws, disconnect the light harness plug and remove light fixture.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If equipped with L.E.D. lights and light burns out, the entire assembly must be replaced.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcsubproc>
